We're just gonna find some guys who sat around watching the state of the world(s) unravel while we desperately sought how to fix it through every means imaginable??? Like Every Means Imaginable??? They just sat around???

My other FFXIV hot take is I think Endwalker was good.... But I think it ended things so nicely I don't think anything they do next will really reel me in for awhile??? Like are we just gonna find something more powerful to fight that just sat around in the background???

It also probably had the best pacing. Every single expansion/post-expansion in FFXIV usually has a few hours worth of gameplay overall where you did nothing because they have to stretch it out, but Stormblood got you moving to new things and big events so much faster.

The worst moment is where you have to quickly escape a crumbling building while a character sacrifices themselves to keep it from falling on everyone, but you just stand around for Ten. Entire. Minutes. Talking. To. Them. Not. Helping. before just running out. It's so poorly done

My Stormblood hot take is just it's maybe the most fun expansion that was a nice "Okay we are dealing directly with the state of the world" story instead of being sucked into some incredibly isolated place, but it is also full of the dumbest moments in the entire video game
